result.name: Tokyo Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text:
Nothing surprise from their food, but it's decent.
You cannot say the food here is great, but they will never disappoint you for average food.  The decoration here is new, food is decent, staffs are friendly.
If you just looking for a daily meal, here is good.  But if you wanna get something new for a great weekend, you better find other restaurant around
Hong Kong style fast food type Japanese restaurant. Don't expect too much, but normally you don't need to wait during lunch hours

The name of the restaurant suggests udon to be their specialty but the menu has very limited choices for udon. The noodle by itself is good (the texture that one would expect for hand-made) but the soup and toppings added together makes only a mediocre bowl.

Decent Japanese food but nothing special. Definitely nothing like Japan and coming from Vancouver, it's not as good as what you can greet in Vancouver, Canada. Not a bad place if you feel like Japanese food.

Very nice and hella cheap restaurant.

I ate the sauce beef and it was very good. I had never eaten something like this before but it still satisfied me a lot. My company ate the Sukiyaki and was also very satisfied. The waiters are nice and it isnt highly frequented. The air conditioning is a bit to cold. The prices are very low. We paid 160HK$ for 2 dishes and 2 drinks.

All in all I would recommend it and if you live near it you should give it a try.
